results.name: Square array T(n,k) (n>0, k>0) read by antidiagonals: if gcd(n,k)>1 then T(n,k)=-1, otherwise T(n,k) = the unique m such that A289815(m) = n and A289816(m) = k.
comment: This sequence, when restricted to the pairs of coprime numbers, is the inverse of the function n -> (A289815(n), A289816(n)).
If n and k are coprime, then the number of nonzero digits of the ternary representation of T(n,k) equals the number of distinct prime factors of n*k.
